data.name: Marina Square
data.description: Marina Square is a shopping mall in Singapore which opened in the late 1980s. It is part of the first building complex built on the reclaimed land at Marina Centre, and was the largest shopping mall in the country at the time.

data.name: Aperia Mall
data.description: APERIA is a landmark integrated development comprising of two Business 1 towers of 17 and 14 storey, and a 3 storey retail podium.

data.name: HillV2
data.description: Close to the city and nestled in Hillview Rise, HillV2 offers a new upmarket retail and lifestyle experience to sophisticated urbanites and families living in the prime locale of Upper Bukit Timah.

data.name: Dhoby Xchange
data.description: Dhoby Xchange is an underground mall connected to Dhoby Ghaut MRT station.

data.name: Havelock II
data.description: Havelock II provides a one-stop solution to its tenants, visitors and shoppers alike with a plethora of gastronomic outlets and office facilities.

data.name: Peace Centre
data.description: Peace centre is located at Sophia Road, it is a hub for printing shops.

data.name: Waterway Point
data.description: Waterway Point is a suburban shopping mall located in the town centre of Punggol New Town, Singapore, next to the Punggol MRT/LRT station. The mall was built as part of Punggol's first integrated waterfront residential and retail development, Watertown.  It is the first mall in Singapore to be integrated with a town square and a visitors’ centre which provides an avenue for residents and the public to learn more about the heritage of Punggol through exhibitions and civic and community events.

data.name: Palais Renaissance
data.description: Palais Renaissance is located at the premium shopping district of Orchard Road, Singapore. Palais has established itself as an exclusive shopping destination which provides an intimate respite amidst the hustle and bustle of the city.

data.name: The Central
data.description: The Central is a mall above the Clarke Quay MRT. It is located next to the Singapore river.

data.name: 85 Redhill Food Centre
data.description: 85 Redhill Food Centre is a 10-min walk away from Redhill MRT Station located in the heart of Redhill.

data.name: 313@Somerset
data.description: A modern, multi-floor mall offering a range of familiar international retailers, with dining options. The 3 unique dining precincts will create a landmark entertainment offer catering to all tastes and appetites.

data.name: Wheelock Place
data.description: is a 21-floor office tower and shopping mall on Singapore's Orchard Road. The mall has an underpass to Shaw House, ION Orchard and Orchard MRT.

data.name: Loyang Point
data.description: Loyang Point is a small neighbourhood shopping mall providing amenities and retail options for the surrounding Pasir Ris neighbourhood.

data.name: Jubilee Square
data.description: Jubilee Square is a former entertainment centre at the Ang Mo Kio Town Centre. It used to house a four-hall cineplex managed by Eng Wah Organization.

data.name: Rivervale Plaza
data.description: Rivervale Plaza is the first shopping complex to be opened in Sengkang New Town.

data.name: Boon Lay Shopping Centre
data.description: Boon Lay Shopping Centre is one of the places where buses to and from Malaysia start and end.

data.name: The Star Vista
data.description: The Star Vista is part of a 15-storey mixed development built in Vista Exchange, one-north precinct. It contains a 5,000-seat auditorium. The Star Vista is connected to Buona Vista MRT.

data.name: NEX
data.description: NEX is the largest mall in North-East Singapore and one of the largest suburban malls in the country, and is integrated with the air-conditioned Serangoon Bus Interchange and Serangoon MRT Station.

data.name: Amoy Street Food Centre
data.description: Amoy Street Food Centre is a two-story hawker centre located in the central business district serving a large office crowd. It is near Telok Ayer and Tanjong Pagar MRT Station.

data.name: Elias Mall
data.description: Elias Mall is a small neighbourhood mall next to Pasir Ris Elias Community Club in containing multiple retail options for the neighbourhood.

data.name: One KM
data.description: OneKM is a mall situated at Tanjong Katong with a multitude of food choices to select from.

data.name: Rivervale Mall
data.description: Rivervale Mall is a suburban grocery anchored retail mall located within the Sengkang new township in the north-eastern part Singapore.  The fully integrated mall has 4 levels of carpark lots that offers a wide mix of retail, lifestyle, healthcare and dining options.

data.name: SingPost Centre
data.description: SingPost Centre the new one-stop lifestyle destination in Singapore’s east that houses the country’s General Post Office, the flagship of a new Smart Post Office network.

data.name: Punggol Plaza
data.description: Punggol Plaza is a shopping mall located in Punggol, Singapore, near Coral Edge LRT Station. The mall is the oldest and one of the first to be built in Punggol to cater to the needs of the residents living there.

data.name: Eastpoint Mall
data.description: Eastpoint Mall is a shopping mall located in Simei, Singapore besides Simei MRT station. At one point it contained Asia's largest pet stop.

data.name: Capitol Piazza
data.description: Capitol Piazza is a mall located along Stamford Road connected to City Hall MRT Station. From primal to the luxurious, where wants turn to needs, Capitol Piazza panders to all who come seeking life’s finer pleasures. With seamlessly connected bespoke zones of retail, dining and entertainment, each promises businesses and customers an experience beyond exceptional.

data.name: Big Box
data.description: BIGBOX redefines Singapore’s retail experience as it runs by factory to store front concept, aiming to surpass customers' expectations by combining an excellent product mix, prices of a warehouse outlet with convenience and service of speciality department stores, making a seamless and pleasurable one stop shopping experience for everyone.

data.name: The Cathay
data.description: The Cathay is a mixed-use 17-storey cinema, shopping mall and apartment building located at Handy Road and Mount Sophia in the Museum Planning Area of Singapore.

data.name: Millenia Walk
data.description: Creating the ultimate in open shopping design, Millenia Walk is a unique lifestyle shopping mall defined by a refreshing burst of colour and an invitingly wide and spacious interior. Visitors may enjoy enriching lifestyle experiences in the mall's aesthetically intelligent environment, designed by Pritzker Architectural Prize Laureate Philip Johnson.

data.name: City Square Mall
data.description: City Square Mall is Singapore’s first eco-mall to be integrated with a 49,000 sq ft (4,600 m2) urban park named City Green. City Square Mall also hosts the world’s first suspended playground.

data.name: The Paragon
data.description: The Paragon is an upmarket shopping centre on Orchard Road, Singapore. With over 200 shops on six floors devoted to fashion, dining, lifestyle, fitness, health and beauty, Paragon has gained a reputation along Orchard Road.

data.name: Orchard Gateway
data.description: Orchard Gateway is the one-and-only shopping mall that straddles both sides of Orchard Road and is linked by a glass tubular bridge and an underpass - forming a "gateway" to the bustling shopping belt.

data.name: The Verge
data.description: The Verge, formerly known as Tekka Mall, was the first and largest modern shopping mall at the Little India precinct in Singapore.

data.name: Thomson Plaza
data.description: Thomson Plaza is a suburban shopping centre located in the heart of private & public residential estates at Upper Thomson Road. It contains 3 shopping levels and a basement carpark. Free valet parking is available during lunch time on weekdays and all day on weekends and public holidays.

data.name: West Mall
data.description: West Mall is a shopping centre located in Bukit Batok, Singapore, next to Bukit Batok MRT Station. It was opened in 1998. West Mall houses a mix of retailers, such as fashion and accessory vendors, jewellery retailers, gifts and specialty stores, telcos, cafes and restaurants, a food court, a six-screen theatre, post office, community library, music school, electrical and household store and a supermarket.

data.name: Junction 9
data.description: Hougang Mall that was previously known as NTUC Hougang Mall, is a suburban shopping mall in Hougang, Singapore.

data.name: Raffles Xchange
data.description: Located at Basement 1 of Raffles Place MRT Station, Raffles Xchange provides a seamless connection from the MRT Station to surrounding buildings such as OUB Centre, Chevron House, Hitachi Tower, Republic Plaza, UOB Plaza and 6 Battery Road.

location.address: 348 Bedok Road Level 2, The Bedok Marketplace

data.name: Golden Mile Complex
data.description: Golden Mile Complex is a high-rise commercial and residential building on Beach Road in Kallang, Singapore. The building was formerly known as Woh Hup Complex. The complex contains 411 shops and 500 parking spaces. The building, much like Lucky Plaza, is largely an ethnic enclave for the Thai population in Singapore.

data.name: Ngee Ann City
data.description: Ngee Ann City is a shopping and commercial centre located on Orchard Road. It currently houses the High Commission of New Zealand in one of the office towers.

data.name: Asia Square Tower 1
data.description: Asia Square is a retail and office building located along Marina View at Marina Bay in Singapore. It is located in Marina Bay, Singapore's new business and financial precinct. It comprises 2,000,000 square feet (190,000 m2) of office space, over 30 entertainment and dining premises, as well as the largest gym in the Central Business District.

data.name: People's Park Complex
data.description: People's Park Complex is a mixed-use development built in the 1970s. The building was the first of its kind in Southeast Asia and Singapore.

data.name: Beo Crescent Market
data.description: Beo Crescent Market is a hawker centre tucked away in Havelock Road. It is a 15 minute walk away from Tiong Bahru MRT Station.

data.name: Paya Lebar Square
data.description: Paya Lebar Square is a 13-storey building with the first three floors designated for shops while the remaining ten floors are for premium office spaces.

data.name: Northpoint City
data.description: Northpoint City is the largest mall in the north housing over 100 dining outlets.

data.name: UE Square
data.description: Since 1996, UE Square has been marked as a historic site by the National Heritage Board. Hailed as an intelligent “city within the city”. UE Square Shopping Mall is a destination mall that brings together retail, entertainment and lifestyle elements in an integrated stop, for the people working, living and playing within the vicinity of River Valley and Clemenceau.

data.name: CHIJMES
data.description: CHIJMES is a national monument awarded the UNESCO Asia-Pacific Awards for Cultural Heritage Conservation. Boasting more than just a rich heritage and stunning architecture, CHIJMES is an exciting gastro-entertainment destination for the discerning patron.

data.name: Hillion Mall
data.description: Hillion Mall, located in Bukit Panjang, is the first mixed-use development in the West to integrate a retail mall, residential living, bus interchange and both MRT and LRT stations at Bukit Panjang.

data.name: Raffles City
data.description: Raffles City is a large complex located in the Civic District within the Downtown Core of the city-state of Singapore. It is built on the site of Singapore's first school - Raffles Institution.

data.name: Concorde Shopping Mall
data.description: Concorde Shopping Mall is close to Somerset MRT Station, Dhoby Ghaut MRT Station and Bras Basah MRT Station

data.name: Lucky Plaza
data.description: Lucky Plaza is a shopping centre located in Orchard in Singapore. Built by developer Far East Organization, Lucky Plaza was completed in 1981 and has proven to be one of the more successful shopping centres in Singapore during its heyday. Lucky Plaza has a range of shops selling electronics, perfume and cosmetics, shoes and sports goods.

data.name: Beauty World Centre
data.description: Beauty World Centre is a mall located along Upper Bukit Timah Road ne

data.name: Mandarin Gallery
data.description: A gem in the heart of Singapore’s shopping belt, Orchard Road, Mandarin Gallery is home to some of the biggest international brands, as well as eclectic finds from independent local offerings.

data.name: Tampines 1
data.description: Tampines 1 is a mall located at Tampines Regional Centre with Tampines MRT and Bus Interchange are nearby. It is the first suburban mall with a dedicated swimming pool.

data.name: Sunshine Plaza
data.description: Sunshine Plaza is a mixed development containing office, retail and housing properties. It has the largest number of printing shops in Singapore. It is close to several MRT stations including Bugis, Bras Basah & Dhoby Ghaut.

data.name: Gek Poh Shopping Centre
data.description: Gek Poh Shopping Centre is a mall in the heart of Jurong West.
